Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: DSL Support Module

Provides comprehensive domain-specific language support for macros including:
- DSL definition and specification
- DSL parsing and interpretation
- DSL code generation and transformation
- DSL validation and verification
- Cross-DSL integration and interoperability
- DSL debugging and development tools
- AI/agent-friendly DSL development
- Production-ready DSL support with error handling

Features:
- Advanced DSL definition with grammar specification
- DSL parsing with custom lexers and parsers
- DSL code generation with multiple backends
- DSL validation with comprehensive error checking
- Cross-DSL integration with translation capabilities
- Comprehensive DSL debugging and development tools
- AI/agent-friendly DSL development and testing
- Production-ready DSL support with comprehensive error handling
:End Note

Note: DSL Types and Data Structures
Type called "DSLSupport":
    context as MacroContext
    dsl_registry as DSLRegistry
    parser_factory as DSLParserFactory
    generator_factory as DSLGeneratorFactory
    validator_factory as DSLValidatorFactory
    debug_tracer as DSLDebugTracer
    performance_monitor as DSLPerformanceMonitor
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "DSLRegistry":
    dsls as Dictionary[String, DSLDefinition]
    parsers as Dictionary[String, DSLParser]
    generators as Dictionary[String, DSLGenerator]
    validators as Dictionary[String, DSLValidator]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

